               </row>
               <row class="- topic/row ">
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(B)</b>
                     </p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">5V(D1238)</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">5V supply ok</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On:</b> The internal 5V power supply is ok.
                        Delivered from the internal 15V power supply.</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Off:</b> Bypass mains not available or there
                        is a hardware issue present.</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Check bypass mains power supply and connection.</p>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Contact <xref
                           conref="../../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/Reality_service_centers"
                           scope="local" class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row class="- topic/row ">
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(C)</b>
                     </p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">15V FAN(D1239)</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry nameend="col6" namest="COLSPEC2" class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p "> Not used</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row class="- topic/row ">
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(D)</b>
                     </p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">24V FAN(D1240)</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">20V supply for EN &amp; fan ok</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On:</b> The 20V power supply used to power
                        supply the static bypass switch EN and the fans is ok. Delivered from the
                        bypass mains.</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Off:</b> Bypass mains not available or there
                        is a hardware issue present.</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Check bypass mains power supply and connection.</p>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Contact <xref
                           conref="../../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/Reality_service_centers"
                           scope="local" class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row class="- topic/row ">
                  <entry morerows="2" class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(E)</b>
                     </p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry morerows="2" class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">STATUS_1(D1242)</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry morerows="2" class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">System firmware status indication</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p "> System firmware status indication. Shows what mode the
                        system is in:<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On:</b> System is in <ph
                           platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/ph ">standby</ph>
                        <ph platform="WxW" class="- topic/ph ">charger only (standby)</ph>
                     </p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Off:</b> Bypass mains not available or there
                        is a firmware or wiring issue present.</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Check bypass mains power supply and connection.</p>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Contact <xref
                           conref="../../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/Reality_service_centers"
                           scope="local" class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row class="- topic/row ">
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Slow flashing (0.5Hz):</b> System is in normal
                        operation.</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry morerows="1" class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Very fast flashing (4Hz):</b> The system is in
                        ISBS operation. There is an issue present with the main controller, or the
                        main controller was manually reset during operation.</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry morerows="1" class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Transfer the system to manual bypass, for details see
                        chapter <xref
                           href="Bruce_How_to_Switch_from_ISBS_Operation_to_Normal_Operation_CPT_0000916382.dita"
                           scope="local" type="concept" class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row class="- topic/row ">
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Fast flashing (2Hz):</b> System is in bypass
                        operation (over the static switch), switched over by the main
                        controller.</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row class="- topic/row ">
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(F)</b>
                     </p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">STATUS_2(D1243)</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">ISBS status ok</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On:</b> The ISBS system is ok and ready
                        transfer to ISBS operation if needed.</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Off:</b> Bypass mains not available or there
                        is a firmware or wiring issue present.</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Check bypass mains power supply and connection.</p>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Contact <xref
                           conref="../../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/Reality_service_centers"
                           scope="local" class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row class="- topic/row ">
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(G)</b>
                     </p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">STATUS_3(D1283)</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">ISBS operation active</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Off:</b> Indicated that the controller has not
                        switched to ISBS.</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">On:</b> The system is in ISBS operation. There
                        is an issue present with the main controller, or the main controller was
                        manually reset during operation.</p>
                  </entry>
                  <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Transfer the system to manual bypass, for details see
                        chapter <xref
                           href="Bruce_How_to_Switch_from_ISBS_Operation_to_Normal_Operation_CPT_0000916382.dita"
                           scope="local" type="concept" class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
            </tbody>
